text: Eunidia brunneopunctata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Per Olof Christopher Aurivillius in 1911. It is known from South Africa, Malawi, Angola, Kenya, Ethiopia, Mozambique, Botswana, Sudan, Namibia, Senegal, the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Tanzania, Somalia, and Uganda.BioLib.cz - Eunidia brunneopunctata.
